bib_record.title: Cross Sections and Recoil Properties of Xenon Isotopes Formed in 11.5-GeV Proton Bombardment of U-238

free_txt: The Measured Cross Sections are Either Cumulative or
Partial Cumulative, Because the Precursors of the Xe
Isotopes Partly Decay Prior to and During the
Xe-Determination. The Correction of the Measured Values
For the Contribution of the Precursors are done Using
Literature Values. In Addition the Cross Sections were
Corrected For Secondary Effects and Zero Target
Thickness. From the Corrected Values Independent and
Cumulative Cross Sections of the Xe-Isotopes and Some
Progenitors are Derived.
. High Sensitivity Mass Spectrometer
A Value of 8.6 Mb at 11.5 GeV was Adopted
